Full name: "ETH>IP>TCP>HTTP2>GRPC"
Description: gRPC server
Example: "Start a gRPC server on port 50051 with this schema: service UserService { rpc GetUser(UserId) returns (User); }"
Startup parameters:
  • proto_schema (required) - Protobuf schema definition. Can be: (1) base64-encoded FileDescriptorSet (recommended), (2) path to .proto file, or (3) inline .proto text
    Example: "syntax = \"proto3\"; package test; service UserService { rpc GetUser(UserId) returns (User); } message UserId { int32 id = 1; } message User { int32 id = 1; string name = 2; string email = 3; }"
  • enable_reflection (optional) - Enable gRPC server reflection (allows clients to discover schema dynamically)
    Example: true

